Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Feb. 22 KYODO -- The government-backed 
Export- Import Bank of Japan signed a loan agreement in Tokyo on 
Tuesday [22 February] to extend a buyer's credit of 4.5 billion 
yen to a public corporation in Colombia, the bank said. 
  Under the agreement, signed with Empresas Publicas de 
Medellin, the loan will be used for purchases of Japanese goods 
and services required for a telecommunications network expansion 
project, bank officials said. 
  This is the bank's third buyer's credit to the corporation, 
following two previous such credits worth a total 11.3 billion 
yen, the officials said. 

